                <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan> Caesari Au</supplied>gusti <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> Divi Iu<supplied reason="lost">li nepoti</supplied> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">principi iuventu</supplied>tis pontifici <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex></expan><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>imp</abbr><ex>eratori</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">vicesimum tert</supplied>ium ann<supplied reason="lost">um <expan><abbr>ingr</abbr><ex>esso</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>def</abbr><ex>uncto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>princ</abbr><ex>ipi</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="4"/>des<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>ign</abbr><ex>ato</ex></expan> Nantuates</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Datierung: nach dem 21.(22.?).2.4 n.Chr.: Todestag des C. Caesar. (B): Walser, Römische: Z. 3-4: [vicesimum tert]ium ann[um ingr(esso) def(uncto) princ(ipi)] / des[ign(ato) Nantuates]; Wiblé 1978: Z. 3-4: [vicesimum tert]ium ann[um ingr(esso) def(uncto)?] / [l(oco)?] des(ignato) [d(ecreto) civitatis ?] oder [Nantuates fec(erunt)?] de s[uo?]; Rosso: Z. 2: co(n)[s(uli) des(ignato)]; Z. 4: [consu]l des(ignatus).</p>
            </div>
